## The POUR Principles

WCAG 2.1 is organized around four foundational principles. All content must be:

### 1. Perceivable
Information and UI components must be presentable to users in ways they can perceive.

**Key Requirements:**
- Text alternatives for non-text content
- Captions and transcripts for media
- Adaptable content structure
- Sufficient color contrast (4.5:1 normal, 3:1 large text)
- Content doesn't rely solely on color
- Text resizable to 200%

**Common Violations:**
- Missing alt text on images
- Insufficient color contrast
- Color-only indicators
- Auto-playing media without controls

### 2. Operable
User interface components and navigation must be operable.

**Key Requirements:**
- Full keyboard accessibility
- No keyboard traps
- Sufficient time for interactions
- No seizure-inducing flashes
- Clear navigation and skip links
- Visible focus indicators
- Touch targets ‚â•44√ó44 pixels

**Common Violations:**
- Keyboard inaccessible controls
- Hidden focus indicators
- Insufficient touch target sizes
- Missing skip links

### 3. Understandable
Information and UI operation must be understandable.

**Key Requirements:**
- Page language declared
- Predictable navigation and behavior
- Input labels and instructions
- Error identification and suggestions
- Consistent UI patterns

**Common Violations:**
- Unlabeled form fields
- Unclear error messages
- Inconsistent navigation
- Confusing instructions

### 4. Robust
Content must work with current and future technologies, including assistive technologies.

**Key Requirements:**
- Valid, semantic HTML
- Proper ARIA usage
- Programmatically determinable names, roles, values
- Status message announcements

**Common Violations:**
- Invalid HTML
- Improper ARIA
- Missing accessible names
- Dynamic content not announced

## Design & Development Guidelines

### Semantic HTML First

Use appropriate HTML elements before reaching for ARIA:

**‚úì Good:**
```html
<button>Submit</button>
<nav>...</nav>
<main>...</main>
<article>...</article>
```

**‚úó Bad:**
```html
<div role="button" tabindex="0" onclick="...">Submit</div>
<div role="navigation">...</div>
```

### Heading Hierarchy

Maintain proper heading structure (h1 ‚Üí h2 ‚Üí h3):

```html
<h1>Page Title</h1>
  <h2>Section</h2>
    <h3>Subsection</h3>
    <h3>Subsection</h3>
  <h2>Section</h2>
```

**Rules:**
- One h1 per page
- Don't skip levels
- Headings describe content
- Not used for styling (use CSS)

### Color Contrast

**Minimum Requirements (WCAG AA):**
- Normal text: 4.5:1
- Large text (18pt+ or 14pt+ bold): 3:1
- UI components: 3:1

**Testing Tools:**
- WebAIM Contrast Checker
- Chrome DevTools Color Picker
- Contrast ratio features in design tools

**Common Issues:**
- Light gray text on white
- Colored text on colored backgrounds
- Button states with poor contrast

### Keyboard Navigation

All interactive elements must be keyboard accessible:

**Keyboard Patterns:**
- `Tab` / `Shift+Tab` - Navigate between elements
- `Enter` / `Space` - Activate buttons/links
- `Arrow keys` - Navigate within components (menus, radios)
- `Esc` - Close modals/menus

**Implementation:**
```html
<!-- Button: works by default -->
<button>Click me</button>

<!-- Custom interactive elements need tabindex and handlers -->
<div role="button" tabindex="0" 
     onclick="handleClick()" 
     onkeydown="handleKeyPress(event)">
  Custom button
</div>

<script>
function handleKeyPress(event) {
  if (event.key === 'Enter' || event.key === ' ') {
    event.preventDefault();
    handleClick();
  }
}
</script>
```

**Focus Management:**
```css
/* Visible focus indicators */
:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid #005fcc;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

/* NEVER do this */
:focus {
  outline: none; /* ‚úó Bad */
}
```

**Focus Trapping in Modals:**
```javascript
// Trap focus within modal
const modal = document.querySelector('[role="dialog"]');
const focusableElements = modal.querySelectorAll(
  'button, [href], input, select, textarea, [tabindex]:not([tabindex="-1"])'
);
const firstElement = focusableElements[0];
const lastElement = focusableElements[focusableElements.length - 1];

modal.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
  if (e.key === 'Tab') {
    if (e.shiftKey && document.activeElement === firstElement) {
      e.preventDefault();
      lastElement.focus();
    } else if (!e.shiftKey && document.activeElement === lastElement) {
      e.preventDefault();
      firstElement.focus();
    }
  }
});
```

### Images and Alt Text

**Decision Tree:**
```
Is the image meaningful (conveys information)?
‚îú‚îÄ Yes ‚Üí Use descriptive alt text
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ Is it complex (chart, diagram)?
‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ Yes ‚Üí Use long description (aria-describedby or linked text)
‚îÇ       ‚îî‚îÄ No ‚Üí Use concise alt text
‚îî‚îÄ No (decorative) ‚Üí Use empty alt="" and aria-hidden="true"
```

**Examples:**
```html
<!-- Informative image -->
<img src="chart.png" 
     alt="Sales increased 45% from Q1 to Q2 2025" />

<!-- Decorative image -->
<img src="decorative-border.png" 
     alt="" 
     aria-hidden="true" />

<!-- Complex image with long description -->
<img src="complex-chart.png" 
     alt="Annual revenue breakdown by region"
     aria-describedby="chart-description" />
<div id="chart-description">
  Detailed description of the chart data...
</div>

<!-- Linked image (alt describes link destination) -->
<a href="/about">
  <img src="logo.png" alt="Company name - About Us" />
</a>
```

### Forms and Labels

**Every input needs a label:**
```html
<!-- Visible label -->
<label for="email">Email Address</label>
<input type="email" id="email" required />

<!-- Visually hidden label (if design doesn't show label) -->
<label for="search" class="sr-only">Search</label>
<input type="search" id="search" placeholder="Search..." />

<!-- aria-label (when label element won't work) -->
<button aria-label="Close modal">
  <span aria-hidden="true">√ó</span>
</button>

<!-- aria-labelledby (reference existing text) -->
<h2 id="dialog-title">Confirm Delete</h2>
<div role="dialog" aria-labelledby="dialog-title">
  ...
</div>
```

**Error Handling:**
```html
<form>
  <label for="email">
    Email Address
    <span aria-label="required">*</span>
  </label>
  <input 
    type="email" 
    id="email" 
    required
    aria-invalid="true"
    aria-describedby="email-error" />
  
  <p id="email-error" role="alert" class="error">
    Please enter a valid email address
  </p>
</form>
```

**Field Instructions:**
```html
<label for="password">Password</label>
<input 
  type="password" 
  id="password"
  aria-describedby="password-requirements" />
<p id="password-requirements">
  Must be at least 8 characters with one number and one special character
</p>
```

### ARIA Best Practices

**ARIA Five Rules:**
1. Use semantic HTML when possible
2. Don't change native semantics (unless essential)
3. All interactive ARIA controls must be keyboard accessible
4. Don't use `role="presentation"` or `aria-hidden="true"` on focusable elements
5. All interactive elements must have an accessible name

**Common ARIA Patterns:**
```html
<!-- Buttons -->
<button aria-label="Delete item">
  <span aria-hidden="true">üóëÔ∏è</span>
</button>

<!-- Toggle buttons -->
<button 
  aria-pressed="false"
  aria-label="Toggle dark mode">
  üåô
</button>

<!-- Expandable sections -->
<button 
  aria-expanded="false"
  aria-controls="section-1">
  Show details
</button>
<div id="section-1" hidden>
  Details content...
</div>

<!-- Loading states -->
<div role="status" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
  Loading...
</div>

<!-- Error announcements -->
<div role="alert" aria-live="assertive">
  Error: Form submission failed
</div>

<!-- Live regions for dynamic content -->
<div 
  role="region" 
  aria-live="polite" 
  aria-atomic="false">
  Search found 24 results
</div>
```

**ARIA Landmark Roles:**
```html
<header role="banner">...</header>
<nav role="navigation">...</nav>
<main role="main">...</main>
<aside role="complementary">...</aside>
<footer role="contentinfo">...</footer>
```

Note: HTML5 semantic elements have implicit roles, but explicit ARIA improves compatibility.

### Skip Links

Provide skip navigation for keyboard users:

```html
<body>
  <a href="#main-content" class="skip-link">
    Skip to main content
  </a>
  
  <header>
    <!-- Navigation -->
  </header>
  
  <main id="main-content" tabindex="-1">
    <!-- Main content -->
  </main>
</body>

<style>
.skip-link {
  position: absolute;
  top: -40px;
  left: 0;
  background: #000;
  color: #fff;
  padding: 8px;
  z-index: 100;
}

.skip-link:focus {
  top: 0;
}
</style>
```

### Responsive and Mobile

**Touch Targets:**
- Minimum 44√ó44 pixels
- Adequate spacing between targets
- Consider larger for small screens

**Orientation:**
- Support both portrait and landscape
- Don't lock orientation unless essential

**Reflow at 320px:**
- Content reflows to single column
- No horizontal scrolling for reading
- Test at 400% zoom

**Text Spacing:**
Content must remain readable with:
- Line height: 1.5√ó font size
- Paragraph spacing: 2√ó font size  
- Letter spacing: 0.12√ó font size
- Word spacing: 0.16√ó font size

## Testing Workflow

### 1. Automated Testing (30-40% coverage)

**Recommended Tools:**
- **axe DevTools** (browser extension) - Most comprehensive
- **WAVE** (browser extension) - Visual feedback
- **Lighthouse** (Chrome DevTools) - Quick baseline

**Integration Testing:**
```javascript
// With Playwright + axe-core
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';
import AxeBuilder from '@axe-core/playwright';

test('page should be accessible', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('/');
  
  const results = await new AxeBuilder({ page })
    .withTags(['wcag2a', 'wcag2aa', 'wcag21aa'])
    .analyze();
  
  expect(results.violations).toEqual([]);
});
```

```javascript
// With Jest + jest-axe
import { render } from '@testing-library/react';
import { axe, toHaveNoViolations } from 'jest-axe';

expect.extend(toHaveNoViolations);

test('Component is accessible', async () => {
  const { container } = render(<MyComponent />);
  const results = await axe(container);
  expect(results).toHaveNoViolations();
});
```

**What Automated Tools Catch:**
- Missing alt text
- Color contrast issues
- Missing form labels
- Incorrect ARIA usage
- Heading hierarchy problems
- Invalid HTML

**What They Miss:**
- Keyboard operability
- Focus management
- Screen reader experience
- Content quality
- Context and meaning

### 2. Keyboard Testing (Manual)

**Test Checklist:**
- [ ] Can reach all interactive elements with Tab
- [ ] Tab order is logical
- [ ] Focus is visible on all elements
- [ ] Can activate all controls (Enter/Space)
- [ ] Can dismiss modals/menus (Escape)
- [ ] No keyboard traps
- [ ] Skip links work
- [ ] Arrow keys work in complex widgets

**Test Script:**
1. Unplug/disable mouse
2. Press Tab to navigate forward
3. Press Shift+Tab to navigate backward
4. Use Enter/Space to activate
5. Use Escape to close
6. Use Arrow keys in dropdowns/menus

### 3. Screen Reader Testing (Manual)

**Recommended Screen Readers:**
- **NVDA** (Windows) - Free
- **JAWS** (Windows) - Industry standard
- **VoiceOver** (macOS/iOS) - Built-in
- **TalkBack** (Android) - Built-in

**VoiceOver (macOS) Quick Start:**
- Enable: `Cmd+F5`
- Navigate: `Ctrl+Option+Arrow keys`
- Interact: `Ctrl+Option+Space`
- Web Rotor: `Ctrl+Option+U`

**NVDA (Windows) Quick Start:**
- Download free from nvaccess.org
- Navigate: Arrow keys
- Read next: Down arrow
- Elements list: Insert+F7

**What to Test:**
- [ ] Page title announced correctly
- [ ] Headings make sense in isolation
- [ ] Form labels announced
- [ ] Button purposes clear
- [ ] Images have meaningful descriptions
- [ ] Error messages announced
- [ ] Dynamic content updates announced
- [ ] Tab order matches visual order

### 4. Visual Testing

**Zoom Testing:**
- Test at 200% browser zoom
- Test at 400% zoom (320px width)
- No loss of content or functionality
- No horizontal scrolling for reading

**Color Contrast:**
- Use browser DevTools color picker
- Test all text combinations
- Test UI component states (hover, focus, disabled)
- Test custom graphics and icons

**Content Reflow:**
- Resize browser to 320px width
- Check single-column layout
- Verify no horizontal scrolling
- Ensure all content accessible

### 5. Component-Specific Testing

**Forms:**
- [ ] All fields have labels
- [ ] Required fields indicated
- [ ] Error messages specific and helpful
- [ ] Errors linked to fields (aria-describedby)
- [ ] Success messages announced

**Modals/Dialogs:**
- [ ] Focus moves to modal on open
- [ ] Focus trapped within modal
- [ ] Escape key closes modal
- [ ] Focus returns to trigger on close
- [ ] Proper ARIA (role="dialog", aria-modal)

**Dropdowns/Menus:**
- [ ] Keyboard accessible (Arrow keys)
- [ ] Selected item announced
- [ ] Expandable state communicated (aria-expanded)
- [ ] Logical grouping

**Carousels/Sliders:**
- [ ] Can pause auto-advance
- [ ] Keyboard accessible controls
- [ ] Current slide announced
- [ ] Number of slides communicated

**Data Tables:**
- [ ] Header cells marked with `<th>`
- [ ] Headers associated with data cells
- [ ] Complex tables use scope/headers/id
- [ ] Caption describes table purpose

## Common Patterns and Solutions

### Pattern: Accessible Modal

```html
<button id="open-modal">Open Settings</button>

<div 
  role="dialog" 
  aria-labelledby="dialog-title"
  aria-modal="true"
  hidden>
  <h2 id="dialog-title">Settings</h2>
  
  <!-- Modal content -->
  
  <button id="close-modal">Close</button>
</div>

<script>
const openBtn = document.getElementById('open-modal');
const closeBtn = document.getElementById('close-modal');
const modal = document.querySelector('[role="dialog"]');
let previousFocus;

openBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
  previousFocus = document.activeElement;
  modal.hidden = false;
  modal.querySelector('button').focus();
  document.body.style.overflow = 'hidden';
});

closeBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
  modal.hidden = true;
  document.body.style.overflow = '';
  previousFocus.focus();
});

// Trap focus, close on Escape (see Focus Trapping section)
</script>
```

### Pattern: Accessible Tabs

```html
<div class="tabs">
  <div role="tablist" aria-label="Settings tabs">
    <button 
      role="tab" 
      aria-selected="true" 
      aria-controls="panel-1"
      id="tab-1">
      General
    </button>
    <button 
      role="tab" 
      aria-selected="false" 
      aria-controls="panel-2"
      id="tab-2"
      tabindex="-1">
      Privacy
    </button>
  </div>
  
  <div role="tabpanel" id="panel-1" aria-labelledby="tab-1">
    General settings content
  </div>
  
  <div role="tabpanel" id="panel-2" aria-labelledby="tab-2" hidden>
    Privacy settings content
  </div>
</div>
```

**Keyboard Behavior:**
- Arrow keys switch tabs
- Active tab is focusable (tabindex="0")
- Inactive tabs not focusable (tabindex="-1")
- Tab key moves to panel content

### Pattern: Accessible Tooltip

```html
<button 
  aria-describedby="tooltip-1"
  onmouseenter="showTooltip()"
  onfocus="showTooltip()"
  onmouseleave="hideTooltip()"
  onblur="hideTooltip()">
  Help
</button>

<div 
  id="tooltip-1" 
  role="tooltip"
  hidden>
  Additional help information
</div>
```

**Requirements (WCAG 1.4.13):**
- Dismissible without moving pointer
- Hoverable (can move pointer to tooltip)
- Persistent until dismissed or no longer valid

### Pattern: Live Regions

```html
<!-- Polite announcement (won't interrupt) -->
<div role="status" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
  <span id="status-message"></span>
</div>

<!-- Assertive announcement (interrupts) -->
<div role="alert" aria-live="assertive">
  <span id="error-message"></span>
</div>

<script>
// Update message
document.getElementById('status-message').textContent = 
  'Form saved successfully';
</script>
```

**Use Cases:**
- Form submission results
- Search result counts
- Loading states
- Validation feedback
- Chat messages

## Remediation Strategies

### Prioritization Framework

**Critical (Fix Immediately):**
- No keyboard access to core functionality
- Severe contrast failures (<3:1)
- Missing form labels
- Broken page structure
- Inaccessible error states

**High Priority:**
- Missing alt text on meaningful images
- Moderate contrast issues (3:1-4.5:1)
- Missing heading hierarchy
- Focus not visible
- Missing ARIA labels

**Medium Priority:**
- Suboptimal focus order
- Minor contrast issues
- Incomplete ARIA implementation
- Missing skip links
- Inconsistent patterns

**Low Priority:**
- Decorative images missing empty alt
- Minor semantic HTML improvements
- Nice-to-have ARIA enhancements

### Quick Fixes

**Missing alt text:**
```html
<!-- Before -->
<img src="product.jpg">

<!-- After -->
<img src="product.jpg" alt="Blue wireless headphones">
```

**Missing form labels:**
```html
<!-- Before -->
<input type="email" placeholder="Email">

<!-- After -->
<label for="email">Email Address</label>
<input type="email" id="email" placeholder="your@email.com">
```

**Poor contrast:**
```css
/* Before */
.text { color: #999; } /* 2.85:1 on white */

/* After */
.text { color: #767676; } /* 4.54:1 on white */
```

**Hidden focus:**
```css
/* Before */
:focus { outline: none; }

/* After - Remove the problematic rule */
/* Or add visible focus */
:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid #005fcc;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}
```

## Platform-Specific Guidance

### React

```jsx
// Manage focus
import { useRef, useEffect } from 'react';

function Modal({ isOpen, onClose }) {
  const closeButtonRef = useRef(null);
  
  useEffect(() => {
    if (isOpen && closeButtonRef.current) {
      closeButtonRef.current.focus();
    }
  }, [isOpen]);
  
  return (
    <div role="dialog" aria-modal="true">
      <button ref={closeButtonRef} onClick={onClose}>
        Close
      </button>
    </div>
  );
}

// Announce dynamic content
function SearchResults({ results, isLoading }) {
  return (
    <>
      <div role="status" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
        {isLoading ? 'Loading...' : `Found ${results.length} results`}
      </div>
      {/* Results display */}
    </>
  );
}
```

### Vue

```vue
<template>
  <button
    @click="toggle"
    :aria-expanded="isOpen.toString()"
    aria-controls="content">
    Toggle Content
  </button>
  
  <div id="content" v-show="isOpen">
    Content here
  </div>
</template>

<script setup>
import { ref } from 'vue';
const isOpen = ref(false);
const toggle = () => isOpen.value = !isOpen.value;
</script>
```

### Angular

```typescript
@Component({
  selector: 'app-button',
  template: `
    <button
      [attr.aria-pressed]="pressed"
      (click)="toggle()">
      {{ label }}
    </button>
  `
})
export class AccessibleButtonComponent {
  @Input() label = '';
  pressed = false;
  
  toggle() {
    this.pressed = !this.pressed;
  }
}
```

