## Key Reminders

1. **Automated testing finds only 30-40%** of accessibility issues
2. **Manual testing is essential** - keyboard, screen reader, visual
3. **Use semantic HTML first**, then ARIA when necessary
4. **Test early and often** - don't wait until the end
5. **Test with real users** with disabilities when possible
6. **Color contrast** is one of the most common failures
7. **Keyboard accessibility** is foundational for many users
8. **Focus indicators** must always be visible
9. **Every interactive element** needs an accessible name
10. **Documentation helps** team consistency and maintenance
